item.title: About
item.description: Hi folks, my name is Alessandro Strino. I have spent a good amount of time securing enterprise networks and products. This blog was born to give something back to the internet community. I’ll try to keep it update with good contents that are related to my area of interest: Reverse Engineering Malware Analysis (Mobile | Windows) Exploit Development About my background… I have took Master’s Degree in Computer Security at University of Salerno, Italy and I also have spent an year at DFire LAB in Dublin as a researcher for my master thesis.
